Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Halve, core, and slice
@bell pepper{1}(halved and sliced into strips) into strips. Trim and halve
@mini cucumber{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise), then cut into 1/4-inch planks.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, @yogurt{2%tablespoon},
juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings), and as much cilantro
and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like until smooth. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add bell pepper, cucumber, and @feta cheese{1/2%cup} to bowl with dressing.
Toss until fully coated.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Lay tortillas on a clean #work surface{}. Spread a thin layer of
@refried black beans{16%ounce} on the bottom two-thirds of each tortilla.
Place veggies on top of refried beans.

Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and
right sides toward filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to
form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal. Divide between #plates{} and serve.